  "body": "### What is wrong?\r\n\r\nWhen we start a sync with a given peer, our `ChainSyncer` requests a chain of (192) headers, in reverse order, starting from our current head, then validates that chain and fetches/stores bodies for them. It does that in order to avoid having to deal with chain reorgs, and although that was a known corner we cut (there's a FIXME comment in the code for it), it is very wasteful specially on a fully synced node as it will end up fetching/processing 192 blocks when we are missing just one block.\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed\r\n\r\nWe could fetch a header chain starting MAX_REORG_DEPTH blocks before our current local head, discard all the ones already present in our DB and process all the others normally",
